# Aktivio — System Rules & Git Workflow

## 🎯 PROJECT OVERVIEW
You are an expert AI developer working on **Aktivio** — a mobile-first PWA web application for teenagers in Bishkek. 
- **Stack:** Next.js (React), TailwindCSS, Leaflet/Mapbox, Supabase/FastAPI, OpenAI API.
- **Target Audience:** Teenagers and youth in Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan. Keep the UI modern, dark-themed (neon accents), vibrant, and highly responsive (mobile-first).

---

## 🔄 CRITICAL GIT WORKFLOW (STRICTLY REQUIRED BEFORE EVERY TASK)
Before you write, modify, or suggest ANY code, you MUST execute and strictly follow this Git automation workflow. Treat this as your primary instruction.

1. **PULL LATEST CHANGES:** 
   Always ensure you are on the latest state of the remote repository:
```bash
   git checkout main && git pull [https://github.com/khatszianAli/AKTIVIO.git](https://github.com/khatszianAli/AKTIVIO.git) main
CREATE A NEW BRANCH:
Never write code directly to main. Create a descriptive feature branch for the current task:
Bash
   git checkout -b feature/aktivio-[short-task-description]
WRITE CODE & IMPLEMENT:
Proceed with the code changes asked by the user, adhering to the codebase style.
AUTO-COMMIT AND PUSH:
As soon as the task is fully completed, functional, and tested, run the following commands to save and upload the work:
Bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "feat(ai): fully implemented [short-task-description] for Aktivio"
   git push [https://github.com/khatszianAli/AKTIVIO.git](https://github.com/khatszianAli/AKTIVIO.git) feature/aktivio-[short-task-description]
Note: After pushing, inform the user of the branch name so they can merge it via Pull Request.
🎨 CODING & STYLE GUIDELINES
1. Frontend (Next.js & Tailwind)
Mobile First: Everything must be fully optimized for mobile screens (simulate smartphone view). Use flex-col, touch-friendly buttons, and proper paddings.
Bishkek Vibe Styling: Use a dark, active theme (e.g., slate-900 backgrounds) with neon colors for categories:
⚽ Sport: Neon Green / Emerald (#10B981)
🎨 Creative: Neon Purple / Indigo (#6366F1)
🏔️ Nature: Neon Cyan / Sky (#06B6D4)
No Placeholders: Write full, production-ready code. Do not use // TODO or leave functions empty.
2. Bishkek Context & Mock Data
When generating mock data for the Map or Threads Feed, use real Bishkek locations and local youth slang (mix of Russian/Kyrgyz: "Магистраль", "Дзержинка", "Джал", "Восток-5", "Асанбай", "байке", "эже", "айс-латте", "топчан").
Keep the app atmosphere alive, fun, and engaging.
3. AI Safety & Error Handling
Wrap all OpenAI API calls or map rendering logic in proper try/catch blocks to prevent the app from crashing during live hackathon demos.
